<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 04 at 3:41PM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of west central Grady
and southeastern Caddo Counties through 415 PM CDT...
At 341 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles northeast of Apache, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 30 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Chickasha, Anadarko, Apache, Cyril, Verden, Cement, Amber, Pocasset,
Norge, Ninnekah, Stecker and Laverty.
This includes Interstate 44 between mile markers 71 and 87.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
